   }

     checkSol[j-1,i-1]<-0
   }
  }

      multiCheat2[pairList[,2]+1,1]))

for(i in 1:nrow(pairList)){

  std2 <- pairList[i,2]
  stdCompare$co11[i] <- length(which(checkSol[std1,]==1&checkSol[std2,]==1))
  stdCompare$co00[i] <- length(which(checkSol[std1,]==0&checkSol[std2,]==0))

  tempString <- paste(temp,collapse = '')
  stdCompare$mxSim[i] <- max(str_count(str_split(tempString,'0')[[1]]))
}

#f

t <- ts(t(Att.Sale.DT[1,15:37]), frequency = 15, start = c(8, 14))
t.train <- window(t,start=8,end=10)
t.test <- window(t,start=10,end=11)

t.meanf <- meanf(t.train,h=6,level = c(85,95))
autoplot(t.meanf)

accuracy(t.meanf$mean,t.test)
##                ME     RMSE      MAE      MPE     MAPE      ACF1 Theil's U
## Test set 809.5556 812.9387 809.5556 20.53467 20.53467 0.3430737  14.83749
t.naive <- naive(t.train,h=6,level = c(85,95))
autoplot(t.naive)

accuracy(t.naive$mean,t.test)
##           ME     RMSE MAE      MPE     MAPE      ACF1 Theil's U
## Test set 142 160.1662 142 3.572728 3.572728 0.3430737  3.132556
t.snaive <- snaive(t.train,h=6,level = c(85,95))
autoplot(t.snaive)

accuracy(t.snaive$mean,t.test)
##              ME     RMSE    MAE      MPE     MAPE      ACF1 Theil's U
## Test set 1072.4 1076.276 1072.4 27.28798 27.28798 0.2232821   18.6885
t.rwf <- rwf(t.train,h=6,level = c(85,95))
autoplot(t.rwf)

accuracy(t.rwf$mean,t.test)
##           ME     RMSE MAE      MPE     MAPE      ACF1 Theil's U
## Test set 142 160.1662 142 3.572728 3.572728 0.3430737  3.132556
t.holt <- holt(t.train,h=6,level = c(85,95))
autoplot(t.holt)

accuracy(t.holt$mean,t.test)
##                 ME     RMSE      MAE       MPE     MAPE       ACF1
## Test set -53.33554 54.49967 53.33554 -1.352546 1.352546 0.07912334
##          Theil's U
## Test set  1.002301
autoplot(t.train) +
  autolayer(snaive(t.train, h=6),series="S.nave", PI=F) +  ##Mean
  autolayer(naive(t.train, h=6),series="Nave", PI=F) +  ##Naive
  autolayer(meanf(t.train, h=6),series="Mean", PI=F) +
  autolayer(rwf(t.train, h=6),series="Random walk", PI=F) +
  autolayer(holt(t.train, h=6),series="Expo smoothing", PI=F)

From the experiment we can see that the exponential smoothing method have the most accuracy.
